%N A395527 Decimal expansion of the median of the probability distribution of areas of triangles formed by selecting independently and uniformly three points at random in the interior of a given square of unit area.
%C A395527 The mode of the distribution is 0 and its mean is 11/144.
%C A395527 The distribution for a parallelogram is the same as that of a square.
%C A395527 Half the real root of (1/3)*x*(20 - 17*x - 34*x^2*log(x)) - (2/3)*(17*x^2 + 8*x - 1)*(1 - x)*log(1 - x) + 2*x^3*log(x)^2 + 4*x^2 *(3+x)*(PolyLog(2, x) - Pi^2/6) - 1/2 = 0.
%H A395527 Norbert Henze, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/3213725">Random Triangles in Convex Regions</a>, Journal of Applied Probability, Vol. 20, No. 1 (1983), pp. 111-125.
%H A395527 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/SquareTrianglePicking.html">Square Triangle Picking</a>.
%e A395527 0.0571563077778520118877918823626695712206103603711742...
%t A395527 RealDigits[(x /. FindRoot[(1/3)*x*(20 - 17*x - 34*x^2*Log[x]) - (2/3)*(17*x^2 + 8*x - 1)*(1 - x)*Log[1 - x] + 2*x^3*Log[x]^2 + 4*x^2 *(3 + x)*(PolyLog[2, x] - Pi^2/6) == 1/2, {x, 1/10}, WorkingPrecision -> 120])/2, 10, Automatic, -1][[1]]
%o A395527 (PARI) solve(x = 1/10, 1/8, (1/3)*x*(20 - 17*x - 34*x^2*log(x)) - (2/3)*(17*x^2 + 8*x - 1)*(1 - x)*log(1 - x) + 2*x^3*log(x)^2 + 4*x^2 *(3+x)*(dilog(x) - Pi^2/6) - 1/2)/2
%Y A395527 Cf. A093072, A093158, A093159, A103281, A103282, A395526.
